I had a mixed experience of this place. It was suggested by one of my colleagues, and since it was so close to my new place in Urbana, I tried it one weekend. The chicken kabab sandwich was amazing. And they have a lot of items to choose from. The gentleman at the counter explained everything so nicely. I was determined to go back and try everything eventually. So the 3/5 is an average of the 5/5 for this experience, and 1/5 for the next one below.  The next experience was terrible. They were about to close at 8, it was 7.50. I had helped someone move earlier and was really hungry. I entered and asked if they were open, the person at the counter said they were, took my order. After the transaction went through and I left a tip, the boss (a different person) said they will close and cannot make food. Which was still okay with me, but then this chap was not able to reverse the credit card transaction. However he paid me cash after 10 mins of futile attempts.  I did give this place another shot. And the falafel sandwich was good. So I'll probably go in and check their other stuff out sometime later. Remember to ask clearly before you order any sandwiches.
